<section id="methodology">
  <h2>02. Methodology</h2>

  <h3>Dataset</h3>
  <p>Golden dataset v{{ dataset_version }} containing {{ total_queries }} queries across {{ categories | length }} categories:
  {{ categories | join(', ') }}. Each query specifies expected technologies and domains for relevance judgment.</p>

  <h3>Systems Under Test</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>System</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for sys in systems_info %}
      <tr>
        <td><strong>{{ sys.name }}</strong></td>
        <td>{{ sys.description }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Metrics</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Description</th><th>Range</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><strong>NDCG@k</strong></td><td>Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain — measures ranking quality with position-aware weighting</td><td>[0, 1]</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>MRR</strong></td><td>Mean Reciprocal Rank — position of first relevant result</td><td>[0, 1]</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Recall@k</strong></td><td>Fraction of relevant items found in top-k results</td><td>[0, 1]</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Precision@k</strong></td><td>Fraction of top-k results that are relevant</td><td>[0, 1]</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>MAP</strong></td><td>Mean Average Precision — average precision across all recall levels</td><td>[0, 1]</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>F1@k</strong></td><td>Harmonic mean of Precision@k and Recall@k</td><td>[0, 1]</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Relevance Judgment</h3>
  <p>A returned node is considered relevant if its technologies or domains overlap with the query's expected technologies or domains (case-insensitive). This matches the evaluation logic established in the project's golden dataset.</p>

  <h3>Reproducibility</h3>
  <p>All results can be reproduced with a single command:</p>
  <p class="mono" style="background: var(--surface-muted); padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 4px;">python -m benchmarks run</p>
  <p>Results are saved as timestamped JSON in <span class="mono">brain/benchmarks/reports/</span>.</p>
</section>
